The proposed Shagunu Beach Resort in Borgu Local Government of Niger State will be bankrolled by a major financial institution, it has been learnt. A statement by Commissioner for Culture and Tourism, Mrs. Chidawa Rifkatu-Adamu, said: “It is the desire of the Governor Abubakar Sani Bello led administration to make Shagunu Beach Resort one of the country’s top tourism sites and a destination of first choice. “Governor Bello has been committed and consistent in driving growth and development in Niger State, and one of his focal points is how to make Shagunu Beach Resort come alive as one of Nigeria’s top tourism sites.” Lead Consultant and Chief Executive Officer of Marcom Support Services Ltd, Mr. Hakeem Akintunde, said it was good the resort has got the attention of a global financial player. He noted that the state had, over three years, embarked on aggressive infrastructural development of communities.   Why Abiodun deserves second term, by aspirant     ‘Be magnanimous in victory’     Honour for ex-Lagos Deputy Governor Adebule, 56 others   He added: “It is our mandate to market and project this resort to the outside world and investors with the hope of making the beach the first in Nigeria and South of the Sahara.” The beach, situated in the widest part of River Niger, occupies 1,000 hectares of land as the river spans 34km across River Niger. Shagunu is a rich natural environment, which projects opportunities to attract further economic development. As a riverside, it portends limitless prospects for positive growth associated with tourism industry development. It links up with Timbuktu in Mali, newly built Baro Ports in Niger State, and connects to the Niger Delta through the water ways. Other side attractions and landmarks of the beach are Kainji National Park, Borgu Games Reserve and Zugurma Games Reserve.